PART B  
Social Media Do’s and Don’ts for College Students 
DO’s: 
• Think before you post; ensure your content is respectful and appropriate. 
• Use privacy settings to control who can see your information. 
• Share accurate and verified information. 
• Maintain a positive and professional online presence. 
• Respect others’ opinions and engage politely in discussions. 
DON’Ts: 
• Do not share personal or sensitive information publicly. 
• Avoid posting offensive, abusive, or inappropriate content. 
• Do not engage in online arguments or trolling. 
• Avoid spreading rumors or unverified news. 
• Do not post content that could harm your academic or professional reputation.
